AB  - Gordon develops a model where he concludes that “the equilibrium value of a firm is a convex function of its leverage rate and … the optimal (value maximizing) policy for all firms is the maximum possible leverage rate’. Using Gordon's model, we show below that Gordon's conclusions are incorrect. We develop a correct version of the Gordon model where the firm's value is invariant to the debt-equity ratio.
