UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0378426684800680
AB  - In his ‘Debt and Taxes’ Miller argued that the value of a firm is independent of its leverage rate and each firm's leverage rate is therefore indeterminate. My paper showed that under the Miller assumptions the value of a firm is a convex function of its leverage rate, and all value-maximizing firms would be at the maximum leverge rate. The Jaffe and Westerfield extension of my analysis established the conditions under which some firms would be at a zero leverage rate. Their analysis does not lead to their statement that ‘the firm's value is invariant to the debt-equity ratio’.
